"title": "7414: priesthood, in NT",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7414",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ recognised the function of the OT priesthood, but the gospel belief in Christ as high priest and the priesthood of all believers superseded the earlier concept.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ acknowledged the role of the Jerusalem priesthood</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:4\">MAT 8:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:44\">MRK 1:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:14\">LUK 5:14</a></p>\n<h2>Characteristics of the Levitical priesthood</h2>\n<h3>It was equivalent to the order of Aaron</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:11\">HEB 7:11</a></strong></p>\n<h3>It was incompatible with membership of the tribe of Judah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:14\">HEB 7:14</a></strong></p>\n<h3>It was not established by divine oath</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:20\">HEB 7:20</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Characteristics of the Melchizedek priesthood</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:15-Heb7:16\">HEB 7:15–7:16</a></strong></p>\n<h2>How Jesus Christ's priesthood resembled the OT priesthood</h2>\n<h3>He fulfilled the requirement of humanity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:17\">HEB 2:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:1\">HEB 5:1</a></p>\n<h3>He was not self-appointed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:4-Heb5:5\">HEB 5:4–5:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>He resembled Melchizedek</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:10\">HEB 5:10</a></strong></p>\n<h2>How Jesus Christ's priesthood contrasts with the Levitical priesthood</h2>\n<h3>It involves a change in the applicability of the law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:12-Heb7:13\">HEB 7:12–7:13</a></strong></p>\n<h3>It lasts for ever</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:23-Heb7:24\">HEB 7:23–7:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:11-Heb10:12\">HEB 10:11–10:12</a></p>\n<h3>It was based on a once-for-all sacrifice, not of animals but of himself</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:26\">HEB 9:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:12\">HEB 9:12</a></p>\n<h3>It is effective, not simply illustrative</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:14\">HEB 10:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:5\">HEB 8:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:1\">HEB 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:4\">HEB 10:4</a></p>\n<h3>It is not that of a mere man, but of the Son of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:28\">HEB 7:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:14\">HEB 4:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:26\">HEB 7:26</a></p>\n<h2>Characteristics of the priesthood of all believers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:9\">1PE 2:9</a></strong></p>\n<h3>They are to reflect the holiness of their great high priest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:15\">1PE 1:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:10\">HEB 10:10</a></p>\n<h3>They are to offer spiritual sacrifices</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:5\">1PE 2:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1\">ROM 12:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:18\">PHP 4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:15\">HEB 13:15</a></p>\n<h3>They are to intercede for others before God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:1\">1TI 2:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:8\">REV 5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:10\">REV 5:10</a></p>\n<h3>They are to represent God before other human beings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:20\">2CO 5:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:7-Eph3:11\">EPH 3:7–3:11</a></p>",
